http://cscope.sourceforge.net/large_projects.html

http://cscope.sourceforge.net/cscope_vim_tutorial.html

cscope -b -q -k -R 

-b -> build database and don't launch cscope GUI
-q -> creates inverted index file that helps with searchig
-k -> set kernel mode (don't look in /usr/include)
-R -> recursive (by default .c and .h files are scanned)
